canonical:
  title: 賀表
  author: 李達衷
  language: lzh
  text: 一人有慶載迴彌月之辰萬國來庭共獻齊天之壽縟儀肅穆佳氣冲融云云智燭幾微仁推惻隱道以德齊以禮盛化難名綏斯來動斯和殊方咸服爰値虹流之旦益膺川至之休云云濱海守封瞻天戀闕離違玉色已幾乎十年頌祝丹心奚止於億載
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀表
  author: 李達衷
  language: lzh
  text: 一人有慶。載迴彌月之辰。萬國來庭。共獻齊天之壽。縟儀肅穆。佳氣冲融。云云。智燭幾微。仁推惻隱。道以德。齊以禮。盛化難名。綏斯來動斯和。殊方咸服。爰値虹流之旦。益膺川至之休。云云。濱海守封。瞻天戀闕。離違玉色。已幾乎十年。頌祝丹心。奚止於億載。
korean:
  title: 하표
  author: 이달충
  language: kor
  text: 한 분이 경사가 있으사 이에 탄강(誕降)하옵신 날이 돌아와 만국이 뜰에 와서 함께 하늘과 같으시도록 성수(聖壽)를 올리오니, 화려한 의식이 엄숙히 거행되고 아름다운 서기(瑞氣)가 엉기어 무르녹나이다. 운운.지혜는 기미(幾微)를 밝히시고 인(仁)은 측은(惻隱)을 미루시며, 덕으로 인도하고 예(禮)로 정제(整齊)하시니 그 성대한 교화[盛化]를 이름짓기 어렵고, 오는 자를 편안하게 하고 움직이는 대로 화목하여 먼 곳이 모두 왕으로 여기고 돌아와 복속을 하니 이제 무지개가 흐른 아침을 만나 더욱 냇물이 흘러드는 복을 받으시나이다. 운운.바닷가에 번봉(藩封)을 지키면서 하늘을 우러러 대궐을 연모(戀慕)하오나 성상의 옥색(玉色)을 못 뵈온 지가 아미 거의 10년이 되오니, 단심(丹心)으로 송축(頌祝)하옴이 어찌 억재(億載)뿐이오리이까.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0210&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Congratulatory Memorial
  author: Lee Dal-chung
  language: eng
  text: |-
    One sovereign graces the realm with blessing, and the day of his noble birth returns once more. Ten thousand nations gather at court, offering together a longevity as boundless as heaven itself. Resplendent ceremonies unfold in solemn majesty, and auspicious emanations shimmer and blend in harmony.

    Wisdom illuminates the subtle mysteries, benevolence extends its compassionate touch, governance flows through virtue, and order is maintained through propriety. Such magnificent transformation transcends all naming. Those who come find peace; all movement achieves harmony. From distant quarters, all peoples render their allegiance. Now, as rainbow light streams forth at dawn, the realm receives ever-greater blessings flowing like waters converging.

    I, guarding these coastal territories as your loyal vassal, gaze upward toward the palace, yearning for the imperial presence. Ten long years have passed since last beholding your luminous countenance, yet my heart remains steadfast as cinnabar. How could my prayers and praises be confined merely to a billion generations?
  footnotes:
    - This is a congratulatory memorial (賀表) presented to a ruler on his birthday, likely by a provincial official stationed far from the capital.
    - The "rainbow light" and "waters converging" are auspicious symbols traditionally associated with imperial virtue and celestial approval.
    - The reference to ten years of separation suggests the author has been serving in a distant posting, physically removed from the court.
